# Plan: monitor section reassembly (Auto → PointerRag) inside existing monitoring

## Context

Auto mode searches documents and then picks a per-query strategy. One of those
decisions, gated by the **Pointer-trigger** slider on the chat bar
(`POINTERRAG_AUTO_GAP_THRESHOLD`), routes the query to **section reassembly**:
instead of feeding the LLM the raw matched chunks, the agent groups them by
`section_id`, calls `Retriever::fetch_section` for each unique section, and
hands those reassembled sections to a strict-grounded LLM call.

Today this routing decision is only visible in three places:

- `tracing::info!("Auto mode: routing to PointerRag …")` and the matching
  `Strict`/`Hybrid` log lines in `backend/src/agent.rs:980-1043`.
- The Auto step-trace message returned to the chat UI per response.
- The Auto info modal in the home page that *explains* the feature.

There are no counters, no histograms, no snapshots, no monitoring-page tiles.
A user tuning the slider can read the message of the last response but cannot
see "of my last 100 Auto queries, how many routed to PointerRag, how often
hydration succeeded vs fell back, what the gap distribution looks like." This
plan adds exactly that, reusing the `rig_stats` blueprint already in the
codebase (atomic counters + ring buffer + snapshot + `/monitoring/agents/...`
endpoint + tile on a monitor page).

## Shape

```mermaid
flowchart LR
  A[agent.rs Auto arm] -->|auto_route → AutoRoute| B[monitoring::pointer_stats::record_route]
  A -->|PointerHydration result| C[monitoring::pointer_stats::record_hydration]
  B --> D[(atomic counters)]
  C --> D
  C --> E[(VecDeque ring buffer<br/>last 100 hydrations)]
  D --> F[snapshot]
  E --> F
  F --> G[GET /monitoring/agents/pointer-stats]
  G --> H[frontend: api::fetch_pointer_stats]
  H --> I[MonitorRag page<br/>Section Reassembly panel]
```

New module is the only writer; agent.rs only `record_*` calls. Snapshot is
read-only and exposed alongside the existing `rig-stats` route. Frontend wires
the snapshot into a new panel on `MonitorRag` (the page where the user is
already looking when they think about RAG behavior).

## Backend changes

### 1. New module: `backend/src/monitoring/pointer_stats.rs`

Model on `backend/src/monitoring/rig_stats.rs` (same atomic + ring-buffer +
`snapshot()` shape). One file, no Prometheus registration needed for v1 —
keep it parallel to `rig_stats` (which is also Prometheus-free).

Atomic session counters:

- `AUTO_QUERIES_TOTAL: AtomicUsize` — every Auto query that reached the
  routing decision (i.e. found chunks).
- `AUTO_ROUTE_POINTER: AtomicUsize`
- `AUTO_ROUTE_STRICT: AtomicUsize`
- `AUTO_ROUTE_HYBRID: AtomicUsize`
- `POINTER_SECTIONS_HYDRATED: AtomicUsize` — sum of `hydrated` across all
  Pointer routes (sections successfully reassembled).
- `POINTER_FB_NO_SECTION_ID: AtomicUsize`
- `POINTER_FB_FETCH_EMPTY: AtomicUsize`
- `POINTER_FB_LOCK_FAILED: AtomicUsize`
- `POINTER_CHUNKS_IN_TOTAL: AtomicUsize` — sum of input chunk counts to
  hydration (denominator for "hydration success ratio").

Ring buffer (last 100 Pointer-routed queries), each entry:

```rust
struct PointerHistoryEntry {
    recorded_at_ms: u64,          // epoch millis, for sort/age
    chunks_in: usize,             // input chunk count
    sections_hydrated: usize,
    fb_no_section_id: usize,
    fb_fetch_empty: usize,
    fb_lock_failed: usize,
    gap: f32,                     // section_ratio − doc_ratio at decision
    threshold: f32,               // gap threshold in effect
}
```

Public API (called from agent.rs):

```rust
pub fn record_auto_route(route: AutoRoute, gap: f32, threshold: f32);
pub fn record_pointer_hydration(
    chunks_in: usize,
    hydration: &PointerHydration,
    gap: f32,
    threshold: f32,
);
```

`PointerHydration` is currently `struct PointerHydration` (private to
agent.rs). Make its visibility `pub(crate)` and add `pub(crate)` to its
fields so `pointer_stats::record_pointer_hydration` can read them without
re-introducing a duplicate type. The struct already has `hydrated`,
`fb_no_section_id`, `fb_fetch_empty`, `fb_lock_failed` — perfect fit.
Likewise expose `AutoRoute` if not already (it is already `pub`).

`snapshot()` returns:

```rust
#[derive(Debug, Clone, serde::Serialize, Default)]
pub struct PointerStatsSnapshot {
    pub auto_queries_total: usize,
    pub route_pointer_total: usize,
    pub route_strict_total: usize,
    pub route_hybrid_total: usize,
    pub pointer_route_pct: f64,        // pointer / auto_queries * 100

    pub sections_hydrated_total: usize,
    pub chunks_in_total: usize,
    pub hydration_success_rate_pct: f64, // hydrated / chunks_in * 100, deduped
    pub fb_no_section_id_total: usize,
    pub fb_fetch_empty_total: usize,
    pub fb_lock_failed_total: usize,

    pub recent: Vec<PointerHistoryEntry>, // newest-first, ≤100
    pub avg_gap: f32,                     // over recent
    pub avg_threshold: f32,               // over recent (reveals threshold churn)
}
```

Re-export ringbuffer entry as `pub` so it serializes for the frontend.

### 2. Register the module: `backend/src/monitoring/mod.rs`

Add `pub mod pointer_stats;` to the module list. No `pub use` re-export needed
— callers will use the full path `crate::monitoring::pointer_stats::...`
exactly like `crate::monitoring::rig_stats::...` does today (see
`backend/src/api/agent_chat.rs:1834`).

### 3. Instrument the routing decision: `backend/src/agent.rs`

In `run_with_mode`'s `AgentMode::Auto` arm (around lines 977–1044):

- Right after `let route = auto_route(...)` and before the `match route`,
  call `crate::monitoring::pointer_stats::record_auto_route(route, frag_gap as f32, gap_threshold as f32);`
- Inside `AutoRoute::PointerHydration` arm, after `let h = self.hydrate_pointer_sections(&used_chunks);`,
  call `crate::monitoring::pointer_stats::record_pointer_hydration(used_chunks.len(), &h, frag_gap as f32, gap_threshold as f32);`

Make `struct PointerHydration` and its fields `pub(crate)` so the monitoring
module can read them. Don't move the type — it stays in agent.rs next to its
producer.

### 4. Expose via existing agentic monitor scope

Edit `backend/src/api/agentic_monitor_routes.rs`:

- Add handler mirroring `get_rig_stats` (lines 1021–1026):
  ```rust
  pub async fn get_pointer_stats() -> ActixResult<HttpResponse> {
      let snap = crate::monitoring::pointer_stats::snapshot();
      Ok(HttpResponse::Ok().json(snap))
  }
  ```
- In `configure_agentic_monitor_routes` (line 1030) add
  `.route("/pointer-stats", web::get().to(get_pointer_stats))` next to the
  existing `rig-stats` route.

Also register the route on the central registry: `backend/src/api/mod.rs`
around lines 824–895. The existing scope already has the `/agents/*` routes
inline; add one matching the rig-stats entry:

```rust
.route(
    "/agents/pointer-stats",
    web::get().to(agentic_monitor_routes::get_pointer_stats),
)
```

(Both registrations exist for `rig-stats` today — match the same pattern.)

### 5. Unit tests in `pointer_stats.rs`

A single `#[cfg(test)] mod tests` block, three tests:

- `snapshot_starts_empty` — fresh module → all-zero snapshot.
- `route_counts_partition_auto_queries` — record one of each route, assert
  totals + pointer_route_pct.
- `hydration_records_history_and_aggregates` — feed two synthetic
  `PointerHydration` values, verify `sections_hydrated_total`, fallbacks,
  recent length, avg_gap.

Counters are process-globals, so guard the tests with a `Mutex<()>` at file
scope (same trick as `chunking_stats` and most other monitoring tests in the
tree); no need to reset between tests as long as deltas are asserted.

## Frontend changes

### 6. API binding: `frontend/fro/src/api.rs`

Add a `PointerStatsResponse` mirroring `RigStatsResponse` (line 2653) plus
the `recent: Vec<PointerHistoryEntry>` ring buffer:

```rust
#[derive(Debug, Serialize, Deserialize, Clone, Default)]
pub struct PointerHistoryEntry {
    pub recorded_at_ms: u64,
    pub chunks_in: usize,
    pub sections_hydrated: usize,
    pub fb_no_section_id: usize,
    pub fb_fetch_empty: usize,
    pub fb_lock_failed: usize,
    pub gap: f32,
    pub threshold: f32,
}

#[derive(Debug, Serialize, Deserialize, Clone, Default)]
pub struct PointerStatsResponse {
    pub auto_queries_total: usize,
    pub route_pointer_total: usize,
    pub route_strict_total: usize,
    pub route_hybrid_total: usize,
    pub pointer_route_pct: f64,
    pub sections_hydrated_total: usize,
    pub chunks_in_total: usize,
    pub hydration_success_rate_pct: f64,
    pub fb_no_section_id_total: usize,
